python3 -m streamlit run app.pys

windows - python -m streamlit run app.py

Storing personal API Keys

1. Pull the latest updates
Open your VS Code terminal and run:

Bash
git pull origin main
2. Create your local secrets folder
In the root directory of our project folder, create a new folder named exactly .streamlit and a file inside it named secrets.toml.

3. Add your free Groq API Key
Go to Groq Cloud Console, make a free account, grab a key, and paste it into your new secrets.toml file exactly like this:

Ini, TOML
GROQ_API_KEY = "gsk_your_actual_key_here"



